    <title>Powers mod Powers</title>

    <introduction>
      <p>
        Main Question: What is the remainder when you divide <m>a^p</m> by <m>p</m>? 
        </p>
    </introduction>



<exercise workspace="50%">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Compute <m>a^p</m> for various values of <m>a</m> and <m>p</m>.  What is your conjecture?
    </p>
  </statement>
</exercise>

<p>
  Find the remainders when you perform the following divisions.  Try different values of <m>a</m>.  
</p>
<exercise workspace="5%">
          <p>
            <m>a^6</m> divided by 10?
          </p>
</exercise>
<exercise workspace="5%">
